Chronic sleep deprivation can stress the heart, increasing cardiovascular disease risk.
A study showed a link between short sleep duration and heart conditions.
Early risers face higher risks of hypertension and strokes.
Athletes benefit from adequate sleep for improved performance.
Adolescents often lack recommended sleep hours due to distractions.
Sleep deprivation affects memory consolidation and hormone regulation.
Elderly individuals with good health rarely report sleep issues.
Lack of sleep can lead to weight gain and health problems.
Women are more susceptible to health risks from sleep deprivation.
Adequate sleep is crucial for overall well-being and disease prevention.
